    %h2#howto How To Pair
    %p.summary
      If you've never paired before, definitely check out 
      = link_to "ping pong pairing", "#pingpong"
      as a way to ease into pair programming.  Using 
      = link_to "TDD", "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Test-driven_development"
      or 
      = link_to "BDD", "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Behavior_driven_development"
      is especially helpful for pair programmers because it provides an agreed, shared goal for making progress.  
      If you don't have a specific test you're trying to pass,
      it's difficult for your pair to provide constructive advice.
